[[File:Mackenzie Large Igneous Province.png|thumb|right|280px|Map of the Mackenzie Large Igneous Province and its sub-features. The Nauyat Formation is shown as "Nauyat volcanics".]] The '''Nauyat Formation''' is a [[Neoproterozoic]]-[[Mesoproterozoic]] [[geology|geologic]] [[formation (stratigraphy)|formation]] located on northwestern [[Baffin Island]], [[Nunavut]], [[Canada]]. It consists of a series of [[continent]]al [[flood basalt]] lava flows of the [[Mackenzie Large Igneous Province]] with a thickness of at least {{convert|360|m|ft|abbr=on}}. These volcanic rocks range in age from 762&nbsp;to 1,221&nbsp;million years old.<ref>[http://rparticle.web-p.cisti.nrc.ca/rparticle/AbstractTemplateServlet?calyLang=eng&journal=cjes&volume=26&year=1989&issue=11&msno=e89-188 Geochemistry of Neohelikian Nauyat plateau basalts, Borden rift basin, northwestern Baffin Island, Canada]</ref>
