{{Solar terms}}
<div style="clear: right; float: right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;">{{Qiufen}}</div>
The traditional East Asian calendars divide a year into 24 [[solar term]]s. '''''Qiūfēn''''', ''Shūbun'', ''Chubun'', or ''Thu phân'' is the 16th solar term. It begins when the Sun reaches the [[celestial longitude]] of 180° and ends when it reaches the longitude of 195°. It more often refers in particular to the day when the Sun is exactly at the celestial longitude of 180°. In the [[Gregorian calendar]], it usually begins around September 23 and ends around October 8.

