'''Reflector (USA-163)''' is a space debris research microsatellite built in Russia by [[NII KP]] for the [[United States Air Force]] Research Lab at [[Kirtland AFB]].<ref name="USA-163B">{{cite web|url=http://claudelafleur.qc.ca/Spacecrafts-2001.html |title=Spacecrafts Launched in 2001 |author=Claude Lafleur |date=2004-10-01 |accessdate=2015-05-27}}</ref>

There has been some confusion about whether or not the USA-163 designation had actually ever been assigned,<ref name="USA-163">{{cite web|url=http://www.satobs.org/seesat/Jan-2002/0169.html |title=SeeSat-L - Milstar 5 on OIG |publisher=Satobs.org |date=2002-01-16 |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref> which appears to stem from the fact that more than one [[microsatellite]] may fly on a given [[launch vehicle]].  A single modern launch may indeed result in multiple maneuvering spacecraft reaching different final orbits.

