[[Category:Artificial satellites orbiting Earth]]

In meteorology, a '''snow day''' is a day on which fall of [[snow]] is observed.<ref>American Meteorological Society Association. [http://amsglossary.allenpress.com/glossary/browse?p=55&s=S].</ref>  A [[meteorological day]] is considered on a different basis from country to country. Most frequently, it refers to the 08.00-08.00 time span (summer time: 09.00-09.00). {{citation needed|date=January 2013}}

