'''Thalassophobia''' ({{lang-el|θάλασσα}}, ''thalassa'', "sea" and {{lang|el|φόβος}}, ''phobos'', "fear")<ref name=OED>{{cite web |url=http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/200078 |title=thalass(o)-, ''comb.&nbsp;form'' |work=OED Online |date=June 2018 |access-date=August 7, 2018 |publisher=Oxford University Press |subscription=yes |quote=from Greek θάλασσα sea, and θαλάσσιος marine, formative elements of learned words.&nbsp;... thalassophobia {{bracket|is}} a morbid dread of the sea.}}</ref> is an intense and persistent fear of the [[sea]] or of sea travel.
Thalassophobia can include fear of being in large bodies of water, fear of the vast emptiness of the sea, of sea waves, and fear of distance from land.<ref name=Snyder>{{cite journal |title=Attack of the Water Monster |journal=Boating |volume=76 |issue=4 |page=44 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NLF-MYBB0BIC&pg=PA44 |first=Kari |last=Snyder |date=2003 |publisher=Hachette Filipacchi Media |location=New York |issn=0006-5374 |quote=Thalassophobia is the fear of the sea and can be associated with the fear of water or waves, fear of the vast emptiness, or fear of distance from land.}}</ref>
